Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Audrey Tran

2023-03-11

My meme

The meme I created was about how time flies for someone who started university in the middle of Covid-19 and was highly inspired from my own experience 

library(magick)
# square one
first <- image_read("https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSyU42IqNsAcWTISECmXEoH3hJ17OtTsr9Xww&usqp=CAU") %>%
image_scale(500)

#square two
firstyear <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                          height = 500, 
                          color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "First year at uni",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 60,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# square three
blink <- image_read("https://ih1.redbubble.net/image.335288186.2522/flat,750x,075,f-pad,750x1000,f8f8f8.u1.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

# square four
blink_text <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                       height = 500, 
                       color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "COVID-19",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 100,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center",
                 weight = 600
            )

# square five

second <- image_read("https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSyU42IqNsAcWTISECmXEoH3hJ17OtTsr9Xww&usqp=CAU") %>%
image_scale(500)

afterblink <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                          height = 500, 
                          color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
image_annotate(text = "Work for\nthe rest of\nyour life",
               color = "#000000",
               size = 60,
               font = "Impact",
               gravity = "center")

# first row
before_Covid <- c(first,firstyear)
top_row <- image_append(before_Covid)

# second row
second_row <- image_append(c(blink,blink_text))

# third row
third_row <- image_append(c(second,afterblink))


meme <- c(top_row, second_row, third_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(800)

image_write(meme,"meme.jpg")

My animated GIF

The GIF was inspired by the similarity of Statistics and Machine Learning since most processes in Machine Learning have a statistical origin. 

library(magick)

# creating each frame, where the text comes from the counts vector
# frame1 
frame1 <- image_read(path="https://i.kym-cdn.com/entries/icons/mobile/000/023/397/C-658VsXoAo3ovC.jpg") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Who are you?" , color = "#FFFFFF", size = 30, weight= 600, gravity = "northwest") 
# frame2
image2 <- image_read(path="https://i.kym-cdn.com/entries/icons/mobile/000/023/397/C-658VsXoAo3ovC.jpg") 
frame2 <- image_flop(image2) %>%
image_annotate(text = "Tell me first" , color = "#FFFFFF", size = 30, weight= 600, gravity = "northwest")
# frame3
frame3 <- image_read(path="https://i.kym-cdn.com/entries/icons/mobile/000/023/397/C-658VsXoAo3ovC.jpg") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "I'm Statistics" , color = "#FFFFFF", size = 30, weight= 600, gravity = "northwest")
# frame4
image4 <- image_read(path="https://i.kym-cdn.com/entries/icons/mobile/000/023/397/C-658VsXoAo3ovC.jpg") 
frame4 <- image_flop(image4) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Why they call me Machine Learning?" , color = "#FFFFFF", size = 25, weight= 600, gravity = "northwest")


frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)

gif <- image_animate(frames, fps = 1) 
gif
image_write(gif,"myanimation.gif")
